benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from invoice item

covered: Valid deletion scenarios: TC01 (remove all), TC02 (remove subset), TC03 (single field), TC04 (no fields), TC05/TC06 (header variations), TC12 (large field set), TC18 (duplicates), TC16 (long header), TC20 (regression header parsing) cover typical success paths and edge cases

Input validation and error handling: TC07 (invalid invoiceItemId format), TC10 (malformed customField), TC17 (partial valid/invalid IDs), TC09 (missing required header) cover validation and error responses
Non-existent and service availability: TC08 (not found), TC14 (dependency unavailable) cover 404 and 503 paths
Authorization and security edge cases: TC19 (expired/invalid token) and TC06/TC09 header variations address authorization headers and 400/204 outcomes
Ad hoc robustness and performance: TC13 (heavy load scenario) and TC20 (header parsing robustness) test resilience and response behavior under stress or unusual inputs
gaps: Explicit concurrency/race-condition testing for simultaneous deletions is missing (no explicit test for two clients deleting the same item concurrently)
recommendations: Add a dedicated concurrency/race-condition test to ensure idempotency and correct behavior under simultaneous DELETE requests
Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient permissions if applicable (beyond 401/unauthorized scenarios)
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests to validate behavior under bursty traffic
Add caching-header validations (ETag, Cache-Control) for DELETE responses if applicable
Add a 500 Internal Server Error test case to complement the existing 503 path and verify server error handling
Broaden authorization coverage with additional token-invalid scenarios (distinct from expiry) and verify appropriate 401/403 responses
